@model HRHelper.Models.JobPosition

<div class="learning-material-container py-3">
    <h3 class="fw-bold mb-4" style="letter-spacing: -1px;">HR Management: Compliance & Onboarding</h3>
    <p class="lead text-muted mb-5">
        Effective Human Resources management balances legal compliance with the strategic integration of talent into the company culture.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-5 opacity-25">

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">1. Legal Framework: GDPR</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">In the modern digital workplace, protecting candidate and employee data is a top priority.</p>
        <div class="bg-dark text-white p-4 rounded-4 shadow-sm">
            <h6 class="text-danger fw-bold text-uppercase small mb-2">Definition</h6>
            <p class="mb-0"><strong>GDPR</strong> stands for <strong>General Data Protection Regulation</strong>. It is a strictly enforced framework in the EU that dictates how personal data must be collected, stored, and protected.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">2. The Employment Contract</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">Transparency between the employer and the employee begins with a clear legal document.</p>
        <div class="p-3 border-start border-danger border-5 bg-light rounded-2">
            <p class="mb-0">The <strong>Employment Contract</strong> is the primary document that outlines the specific terms of employment, including responsibilities, salary, working hours, and notice periods.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">3. Purpose of the Probation Period</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">Hiring is a high-stakes decision. The first few months are critical for both parties.</p>
        <div class="alert alert-secondary border-0 rounded-4 shadow-sm">
            <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
            The typical purpose of a <strong>probation period</strong> is to <strong>evaluate the fit and performance</strong> of a new hire before the commitment becomes permanent.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">4. Assessing Technical Talent</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">Generic interviews often fail to identify true technical proficiency.</p>
        <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="p-4 border rounded-4 bg-white shadow-sm">
                    <p class="mb-0">When hiring developers, the most effective assessment tools are <strong>coding challenges and technical interviews</strong>. These provide objective evidence of a candidate's problem-solving logic and syntax knowledge.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">5. What is Onboarding?</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">Employee retention starts on day one. A good start leads to long-term success.</p>
        <div class="p-3 bg-danger text-white rounded-4">
            <p class="mb-0"><strong>Onboarding</strong> is the comprehensive process of <strong>integrating a new employee into the company</strong>. It goes beyond paperwork, focusing on introducing tools, culture, and team dynamics.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">6. Anti-Discrimination Practices</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">Fairness is not just an ethical requirement; it's a competitive advantage.</p>
        <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm rounded-4 overflow-hidden">
            <div class="card-body p-4 border-top border-5 border-dark">
                <p class="mb-0"><strong>Equal Opportunity Hiring</strong> is a key anti-discrimination practice. It ensures that candidates are evaluated solely on their merits, skills, and potential, regardless of age, gender, race, or marital status.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>